==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoax
<hw>Hoax</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. contr. fr.
<ets>hocus</ets>, in <ets>hocus-pocus</ets>.]</ety> <def>A deception for
mockery or mischief; a deceptive trick or story; a practical joke.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoax</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hoax
<hw>Hoax</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hoaxed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hoaxing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To deceive by a story or a trick,
for sport or mischief; to impose upon sportively.</def>
<rj><au>Lamb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoaxer</ent>⟦br⟧
